  "passage": {
    "text": "As we previously noted, sustained investment demand and robust central bank purchases are essential for gold prices to remain above USD 4,000/ oz. We expect central bank purchases to remain elevated\u2014within the 750-1,000 metric ton range for the full year\u2014supported by a long-term desire to hold less USD assets. But while these flows are helpful for price stabilization, they are insufficient to drive prices higher. More clarity on central bank purchases will come with the World Gold Council 2Q Gold Demand Trends report.",
